cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper discusses a journal evaluation tool that uses an iterative algorithm to weight citations, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely candidates as they deal with information retrieval and ranking algorithms. Additionally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) may be relevant as the paper discusses the impact of journal rankings. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be relevant as the Eigenfactor algorithm is based on network analysis. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may be relevant as the paper discusses the validity of different methods for calculating journal impact, which is relevant to the evaluation of research in the field of cryptography and security.
